StartFragment

I’ve already added a set of new trigger keywords to capture manual replies such as:

- \
  "Ok"\
- \
  "Okay"\
- \
  "Yes please"\
- \
  "This is me"\
- \
  "That's me"\
- \
  "How can I help you?"\
- \
  "How may I help?"\

This ensures that your replies will now be processed correctly and trigger the second message, adding leads to the opportunity pipeline.

The reason I didn’t implement a completely new automation specifically for manual replies is that it could potentially interfere with our existing **Automation 2**, which already manages responses from keywords like "YES" and triggers the follow-up actions accordingly. Adding a new automation for manual replies would risk causing conflicts or overlapping with the current workflows, which could disrupt the overall process.

Instead, by adding the new keywords to **Automation 2**, I’ve ensured that manual replies are captured without affecting the existing workflow. This way, the system remains efficient and consistent, and leads who respond manually will still receive the second follow-up message and be added to the opportunity pipeline.

To prevent this issue from occurring in the future, we will continue to add more keywords over time to ensure all relevant manual responses are captured and processed smoothly.

EndFragment
